transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling VasaSite. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I was just trying to order some VasaSite online.

Speaker 1: I did it from the ad that you had on there, but I didn't have a confirmation for my order or anything.

Speaker 2: It just started showing that I could order more for a discounted price,

Speaker 1: but it didn't tell me if my order went through.

Speaker 2: So if that shows up, it does mean the order went through.

Speaker 1: But if I get your name, I can double-check for you.

Speaker 2: But if you saw that screen, it means it went through.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay, because I didn't know if I had – because it was saying that I could get, like, a six-month…

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah, I know what pops up.

Speaker 1: Yeah, some people like to stock up, and we offer discounted rates after you make a regular purchase.

Speaker 2: But I can confirm the order if I just get your name.

Speaker 1: Okay, my name is – first name is Blas, B-L-A-S.

Speaker 2: Last name is Lozano, L-O-Z-A-N-O. That's Z as in zebra.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Rose Avenue?

Speaker 1: Rose Avenue, correct, Beaumont, California.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you wanted buy three, get three free, right, for a total of six?

Speaker 1: Correct, correct. Yes, total of six.

Speaker 2: Okay, and it went through successfully.

Speaker 1: They should be sending you an email shortly confirming that your order did go through.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 1: It just confused me because it didn't say that my order went through or anything.

Speaker 2: It just went through that other process.

Speaker 1: I got you.

Speaker 2: Thank you. That's all I wanted to know.

Speaker 1: Of course. Have a good one.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you. Okay, bye.
